<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Aandain on 04-03-2001 07:36 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I have set up a hotkey bank to be able to get to the pages I need quickly. Some of the pages have blank spots, but you don't have to worry about flipping back 20 pages when you only have to hit one hotkey.

Main (/book 1) All my heals that I currently typically use (Greater/ Superior/ Complete/ Group), Valor, Guard, Root, Stuns.

2nd (/book 3) Backup spells, not used as often as the first set. Symbol (will have 2 symbols here when I get the peridot version), atone, bind, gate, stuff like that.

Resist (/book 5) One side has all my resists, the other side has all my cures.

DD (/book 7) Not just DD, but I know what I mean. Has one side with my undead DD and fears, other side with my regular DD, AoE DD (even if I never use it), and regular and AoE fears

Summon (/book 9) I haven't bought food since I was a newbie, and I don't want to start now. Summon food, water, hammer.

Misc (/book 11) Stuff that doesn't fit anywhere else, extinguish fatigue is the one I end up using most from here. Other various buffs or whatever, like the imbue gem spell, that haven't been made obsolete by higher level spells, but I rarely use.

Way in the back about /book 20 is where I start piling all the earlier versions of the spell lines. Rarely ever go back here, except when I feel like practicing conjuration and want to cast single foods or waters while waiting on a boat or something.

I usually end up doing some shuffling every new set of spells, but that's part of the fun of getting them.

Oh, and my #10 hotkey is /sit off, which is what it is on my primary hotkey bank as well, (with all my characters, usually), so I don't have to think about it.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
